
Native to San Diego, Californian, Juli Ann Blanco is a Public Art/Mural Artist and painter.  She is also an art educator working with all ages.  She is affiliated with Yolo County Arts of Woodland, California and teaches art in Yolo County schools.  Julis artistic contributions in Davis have been well received and respected.  She was given the opportunity by the City of Davis to create new public art Artist Benches in the neighborhood of Wildhorse on Wright Boulevard just off of Covell Boulevard Covell in west Davis.  So far two have been completed.  Passionate Pablo is the name of one of the benches and Visionary Vincent is the other.  Juli Ann pays tribute to Pablo Picasso and Vincent VanGogh in these colorful, functional public art pieces.
